<td>Free (your time)</td>
<td>Varies</td>
<td>High</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>No transcript</td>
<td>$0</td>
<td>N/A</td>
<td>Zero</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<p>Publish the full transcript on your episode page. Do not hide it behind a toggle or accordion by default. Search engines need to see the text in the page source to index it. You can use a "Read Full Transcript" expand section, but make sure the text is in the HTML on initial page load.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Podcast transcript SEO impact. Comparison of approaches" src="/images/blog/podcast-transcript-seo-methods.webp" /></p>
<h3>Clean Up Transcripts for Readability</h3>
<p>Raw AI transcripts include filler words, false starts, and awkward phrasing. Clean them up:</p>
<ul>
<li>Remove "um," "uh," "you know," and repeated words</li>
<li>Add paragraph breaks every 3-4 sentences</li>
<li>Insert H2 headings for major topic shifts</li>
<li>Bold key takeaways and statistics</li>
<li>Add speaker labels for multi-person episodes</li>
</ul>
<p>A cleaned transcript doubles as a written version of your episode. Some readers prefer text. Others scan for specific sections. Both behaviors increase time on page, which supports your SEO.</p>
